git add . - Adds EVERYTHING in this location to the staging area 

git restore --staged <file name> to remove from staging area

touch .gitignore (creating a file to specify what we want guit to ignore)

Exercise - Create the files password.txt, secrets.md, keys, hello.txt
Create a .gitignore that ignores all of the files apart from hello.txt 

# Ignore this file
<name of file>

# Ignore all file types ending in this
*.txt

# Ignore all files called hello that end in different things
hello.*

# ! to reverse the rules for a specific file
!hello.txt
